Anthrax, Italy
----------
Information received on 29 Oct 2014 from Prof. Dr. Romano Marabelli, Chief Veterinary Officer, Secretary General, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Oct 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 13 Oct 2014
Report date: 29 Oct 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 29 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Oct 2012
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1 (2014/2): Agira, ENNA, SICILIA
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Oct 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 170 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 170 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [in percentages]:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.59 / 0.59 / 100.00 / 0.59
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures:
Measures applied:
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
No vaccination
No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Experimental Zooprophilactic Institute - Foggia (National laboratory) / Cattle / direct immunofluorescence (DIF) test / 13 Oct 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [This shows the outbreak in the centre of Sicily. - Mod.MHJ].

