Anthrax - Italy
-------------
Information received on 29 Oct 2014 from Prof. Dr. Romano Marabelli, Chief Veterinary Officer, Secretary General, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Sep 2014
Report date: 29 Oct 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 29 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Oct 2012
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (2)

Outbreak 1 (2014/1): Lagonegro, POTENZA, BASILICATA
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2014
Outbreak status: Resolved (30 Sep 2014)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 11 / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The positivity regards animals found dead on a pasture.

Outbreak 2 (2014/3): Tramutola, POTENZA, BASILICATA
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Oct 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 198 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 209 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [in percentages]:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.44 / 1.44 / 100.00 / 1.44
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection:
Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied:
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
No vaccination
No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied:
No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Experimental Zooprophilactic Institute - Foggia (National laboratory) / Cattle / pathogen isolation on cell culture / 8 Sep 2014 / Positive
Experimental Zooprophilactic Institute - Foggia (National laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 17 Oct 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [See map for locations of outbreaks in southern Italy. - Mod.MHJ]

